TagHelpers.Documentation:
<summary>
             Combines the behaviors of <see cref="T:Microsoft.AspNetCore.Components.Authorization.AuthorizeView" /> and <see cref="T:Microsoft.AspNetCore.Components.RouteView" />,
             so that it displays the page matching the specified route but only if the user
             is authorized to see it.
            
             Additionally, this component supplies a cascading parameter of type <see cref="T:System.Threading.Tasks.Task`1" />,
             which makes the user's current authentication state available to descendants.
             </summary>

            Gets or sets a value that determines how many additional items will be rendered
            before and after the visible region. This help to reduce the frequency of rendering
            during scrolling. However, higher values mean that more elements will be present
            in the page.
            </summary>

BoundAttributes.Name: SpacerElement
BoundAttributes.Documentation:
<summary>
             Gets or sets the tag name of the HTML element that will be used as the virtualization spacer.
             One such element will be rendered before the visible items, and one more after them, using
             an explicit "height" style to control the scroll range.
            
             The default value is "div". If you are placing the <see cref="T:Microsoft.AspNetCore.Components.Web.Virtualization.Virtualize`1" /> instance inside
             an element that requires a specific child tag name, consider setting that here. For example when
             rendering inside a "tbody", consider setting <see cref="P:Microsoft.AspNetCore.Components.Web.Virtualization.Virtualize`1.SpacerElement" /> to the value "tr".
             </summary>

BoundAttributes.Name: Context
BoundAttributes.Documentation: Specifies the parameter name for all child content expressions.

            The text color of the labels. Accepts a valid CSS color string, including hex and rgb.
            </summary>

BoundAttributes.Name: Font
BoundAttributes.Documentation:
<summary>
            The font style of the labels. Accepts a valid CSS color string, for example "20px 'Courier New'".
            </summary>

BoundAttributes.Name: Format
BoundAttributes.Documentation:
<summary>
            The format used to display the labels. Uses kendo.format. Contains one placeholder ("{0}") which represents the category value.
            </summary>

BoundAttributes.Name: Mirror
BoundAttributes.Documentation:
<summary>
            If set to true the chart will mirror the axis labels and ticks. If the labels are normally on the left side of the axis, mirroring the axis will render them to the right.
            </summary>

BoundAttributes.Name: Skip
BoundAttributes.Documentation:
<summary>
            The number of labels to skip. By default no labels are skipped.
            </summary>

BoundAttributes.Name: Step
BoundAttributes.Documentation:
<summary>
            The label rendering step - render every n-th label. By default every label is rendered.
            </summary>

BoundAttributes.Name: Template
BoundAttributes.Documentation:
<summary>
            The template which renders the labels.The fields which can be used in the template are: value - the category value; dataItem - the data item, in case a field has been specified. If the category does not have a corresponding item in the data then an empty object will be passed.; format - the default format of the label or culture - the default culture (if set) on the label.
            </summary>

BoundAttributes.Name: Visible
BoundAttributes.Documentation:
<summary>
            If set to true the chart will display the category axis labels. By default the category axis labels are visible.
            </summary>

BoundAttributes.Name: Position
BoundAttributes.Documentation:
<summary>
            Specifies the position of the labels.
            </summary>

BoundAttributes.Documentation:
<summary>
            The background color of the legend. Accepts a valid CSS color string, including hex and rgb.
            </summary>

BoundAttributes.Name: Height
BoundAttributes.Documentation:
<summary>
            The legend height when the legend.orientation is set to "vertical".
            </summary>

BoundAttributes.Name: OffsetX
BoundAttributes.Documentation:
<summary>
            The X offset of the chart legend. The offset is relative to the default position of the legend. For instance, a value of 20 will move the legend 20 pixels to the right of its initial position. A negative value will move the legend to the left of its current position.
            </summary>

BoundAttributes.Name: OffsetY
BoundAttributes.Documentation:
<summary>
            The Y offset of the chart legend.  The offset is relative to the current position of the legend. For instance, a value of 20 will move the legend 20 pixels down from its initial position. A negative value will move the legend upwards from its current position.
            </summary>

BoundAttributes.Name: Reverse
BoundAttributes.Documentation:
<summary>
            If set to true the legend items will be reversed.Available in versions 2013.3.1306 and later.
            </summary>

BoundAttributes.Name: Spacing
BoundAttributes.Documentation:
<summary>
            The spacing between the labels in pixels when the legend.orientation is "horizontal".
            </summary>

BoundAttributes.Name: Visible
BoundAttributes.Documentation:
<summary>
            If set to true the chart will display the legend. By default the chart legend is visible.
            </summary>

BoundAttributes.Name: Width
BoundAttributes.Documentation:
<summary>
            The legend width when the legend.orientation is set to "horizontal".
            </summary>

BoundAttributes.Name: Align
BoundAttributes.Documentation:
<summary>
            Specifies the legend align.
            </summary>

BoundAttributes.Name: Orientation
BoundAttributes.Documentation:
<summary>
            Specifies the legend orientation.
            </summary>

BoundAttributes.Name: Position
BoundAttributes.Documentation:
<summary>
            Specifies the legend position.
            </summary>

BoundAttributes.Name: AutoFit
BoundAttributes.Documentation:
<summary>
            If set to true, the Chart automatically scales down to fit the content area. Applicable for the Pie and Donut series (see example).
            </summary>

BoundAttributes.Name: Axis
BoundAttributes.Documentation:
<summary>
            The name of the value axis to use.
            </summary>

BoundAttributes.Name: CategoryAxis
BoundAttributes.Documentation:
<summary>
            The name of the category axis to use for the series.The first axis will be used if no categoryAxis is specified.
            </summary>

BoundAttributes.Name: CategoryField
BoundAttributes.Documentation:
<summary>
            The data item field which contains the category name or date.
            </summary>

BoundAttributes.Name: CloseField
BoundAttributes.Documentation:
<summary>
            The data field containing the close value.
            </summary>

BoundAttributes.Name: Color
BoundAttributes.Documentation:
<summary>
            The series base color. The supported values are: CSS color string, including hex and rgb or function(point) - user-defined function that will be evaluated for each point. Returning undefined will assume the default series color..
            </summary>

BoundAttributes.Name: ColorField
BoundAttributes.Documentation:
<summary>
            The data item field which contains the series color.
            </summary>

BoundAttributes.Name: DownColor
BoundAttributes.Documentation:
<summary>
            The series color when the open value is greater than the close value.
            </summary>

BoundAttributes.Name: DownColorField
BoundAttributes.Documentation:
<summary>
            The data field containing the color applied when the open value is greater than the close value.
            </summary>

BoundAttributes.Name: ExplodeField
BoundAttributes.Documentation:
<summary>
            The data item field which contains a boolean value indicating whether the sector is exploded.
            </summary>

BoundAttributes.Name: Field
BoundAttributes.Documentation:
<summary>
            The data item field which contains the series value. The field name should be a valid Javascript identifier and should contain only alphanumeric characters (or "$" or "_"), and may not start with a digit.
            </summary>

BoundAttributes.Name: Gap
BoundAttributes.Documentation:
<summary>
            The distance between categories expressed as a percentage of the bar width.See the related spacing setting.
            </summary>

BoundAttributes.Name: HighField
BoundAttributes.Documentation:
<summary>
            The data field containing the high value.
            </summary>

BoundAttributes.Name: HoleSize
BoundAttributes.Documentation:
<summary>
            The diameter of the donut hole in pixels.
            </summary>

BoundAttributes.Name: LowField
BoundAttributes.Documentation:
<summary>
            The data field containing the low value.
            </summary>

BoundAttributes.Name: Margin
BoundAttributes.Documentation:
<summary>
            The margin around each donut series (ring). A numeric value will set all margins.
            </summary>

BoundAttributes.Name: Name
BoundAttributes.Documentation:
<summary>
            The name of the chart series which is visible in the legend.
            </summary>

BoundAttributes.Name: NegativeColor
BoundAttributes.Documentation:
<summary>
            The color to use for bar, column or waterfall series with negative values. Accepts a valid CSS color string, including hex and rgb.
            </summary>

BoundAttributes.Name: Opacity
BoundAttributes.Documentation:
<summary>
            The series opacity. By default the series are opaque.
            </summary>

BoundAttributes.Name: OpenField
BoundAttributes.Documentation:
<summary>
            The data field containing the open value.
            </summary>

BoundAttributes.Name: Padding
BoundAttributes.Documentation:
<summary>
            The padding around the chart (equal on all sides).
            </summary>

BoundAttributes.Name: Size
BoundAttributes.Documentation:
<summary>
            The or radius of the chart donut series in pixels. If not set, the available space is split evenly between the series.
            </summary>

BoundAttributes.Name: SizeField
BoundAttributes.Documentation:
<summary>
            The data field containing the bubble size value.
            </summary>

BoundAttributes.Name: Spacing
BoundAttributes.Documentation:
<summary>
            The distance between series points within a category. Expressed as a percentage of the bar width.See the related gap setting.
            </summary>

BoundAttributes.Name: StartAngle
BoundAttributes.Documentation:
<summary>
            The start angle (degrees) of the first donut or pie segment.Angles increase clockwise and zero is to the left. Negative values are acceptable.
            </summary>

BoundAttributes.Name: Visible
BoundAttributes.Documentation:
<summary>
            Sets the visible property of a chart series
            </summary>

BoundAttributes.Name: VisibleInLegend
BoundAttributes.Documentation:
<summary>
            A value indicating whether to show the point category name (for funnel, donut and pie series) or series name (for other available series types) in the legend.
            </summary>

BoundAttributes.Name: VisibleInLegendField
BoundAttributes.Documentation:
<summary>
            The data item field which indicates whether to show the point category name in the legend.
            </summary>

BoundAttributes.Name: XAxis

<summary>

            </summary>

BoundAttributes.Documentation:
<summary>
            The data item field containing the X value.
            </summary>

BoundAttributes.Name: YAxis
BoundAttributes.Documentation:

BoundAttributes.Name: YField
BoundAttributes.Documentation:
<summary>

            </summary>

BoundAttributes.Name: ZIndex
BoundAttributes.Documentation:
<summary>
            An optional Z-index that can be used to change the default stacking order of series.The series with the highest Z-index will be placed on top.Series with no Z-index will use the default stacking order based on series type. For example line series will be on top with bar and area following below.
            </summary>

<summary>
            Telerik UI ChartSeriesLabels.
            </summary>

BoundAttributes.Name: Background
BoundAttributes.Documentation:
<summary>
            The background color of the labels. Accepts a valid CSS color string, including hex and rgb.
            </summary>

BoundAttributes.Name: Color
BoundAttributes.Documentation:
<summary>
            The text color of the labels. Accepts a valid CSS color string, including hex and rgb.
            </summary>

BoundAttributes.Name: Distance
BoundAttributes.Documentation:
<summary>
            The distance of the labels when series.type is set to "donut" or "pie".
            </summary>

BoundAttributes.Name: Font
BoundAttributes.Documentation:
<summary>
            The font style of the labels. Accepts a valid CSS color string, for example "20px 'Courier New'".
            </summary>

BoundAttributes.Name: Format
BoundAttributes.Documentation:
<summary>
            The format of the labels. Uses kendo.format.
            </summary>

BoundAttributes.Name: Rotation
BoundAttributes.Documentation:
<summary>
            The rotation angle of the labels. By default, the labels are not rotated.
            </summary>

BoundAttributes.Name: Template
BoundAttributes.Documentation:
<summary>
            The template which renders the chart series label.The fields which can be used in the template are: category - the category name. Available for area, bar, column, bubble, donut, line, pie and waterfall series.; dataItem - the original data item used to construct the point. Will be null if binding to array.; percentage - the point value represented as a percentage value. Available only for donut, pie and 100% stacked charts.; series - the data series; stackValue - the cumulative point value on the stack. Available only for stackable series.; value - the point value. Can be a number or object containing each bound field.; runningTotal - the sum of point values since the last "runningTotal" summary point. Available for waterfall series. or total - the sum of all previous series values. Available for waterfall series..
            </summary>

BoundAttributes.Name: Visible
BoundAttributes.Documentation:
<summary>
            If set to true the chart will display the series labels. By default chart series labels are not displayed.
            </summary>

BoundAttributes.Name: Align
BoundAttributes.Documentation:
<summary>
            Specifies the alignment of the labels.
            </summary>

BoundAttributes.Name: Position
BoundAttributes.Documentation:
<summary>
            Specifies the position of the labels.
            </summary>

BoundAttributes.Name: DashType
BoundAttributes.Documentation:
<summary>
            The dash type of the border.The following dash types are supported: "dash" - a line consisting of dashes; "dashDot" - a line consisting of a repeating pattern of dash-dot; "dot" - a line consisting of dots; "longDash" - a line consisting of a repeating pattern of long-dash; "longDashDot" - a line consisting of a repeating pattern of long-dash-dot; "longDashDotDot" - a line consisting of a repeating pattern of long-dash-dot-dot or "solid" - a solid line.
            </summary>

BoundAttributes.Name: Width
BoundAttributes.Documentation:
<summary>
            The width of the border in pixels. By default the border width is set to zero which means that the border will not appear.
            </summary>

<summary>

            </summary>

BoundAttributes.Documentation:
<summary>

            </summary>

BoundAttributes.Documentation:

            The unique axis name. Used to associate a series with a x axis using the series.xAxis option.

            </summary>

BoundAttributes.Name: Data
BoundAttributes.Documentation:
<summary>
            Array of data items. The data item type can be either a: Array of objects. Each point is bound to the specified series fields.; Array of numbers. Available for area, column and line series. or Array of arrays of numbers. Available for:OHLC and candlestick series (open, high, low, close).
            </summary>

BoundAttributes.Name: HighField
BoundAttributes.Documentation:
<summary>
            The data field containing the high value.** Available for candlestick and ohlc series only **
            </summary>

            </summary>

            </summary>

BoundAttributes.Name: Name
BoundAttributes.Documentation:
<summary>
            The navigator series name.
            </summary>

BoundAttributes.Name: Aggregate
BoundAttributes.Documentation:
<summary>
            The aggregate function to apply for date series.This function is used when a category (an year, month, etc.) contains two or more points. The function return value is displayed instead of the individual points.The supported values are: "avg" - the average of all values for the date period.; "count" - the number of values for the date period.; "max" - the highest value for the date period.; "min" - the lowest value for the date period.; "sum" - the sum of all values for the date period. Defaults to 0 if no data points are defined.; "sumOrNull" - the sum of all values for the date period. Defaults to null if no data points are defined.; "first" - the first value; function(values, series, dataItems, category) - user-defined aggregate function. Returns single value or data item. or object  - (compound aggregate) Applicable to "candlestick" and ohlc "series". Specifies the aggregate for each data item field..
            </summary>

BoundAttributes.Documentation:
<summary>
            The name of the value axis to use.** Applicable to area, column, line, ohlc and candlestick series **
            </summary>

BoundAttributes.Name: CloseField
BoundAttributes.Documentation:
<summary>
            The data field containing the close value.** Available for candlestick and ohlc series only **
            </summary>

BoundAttributes.Name: Color
BoundAttributes.Documentation:
<summary>
            The series base color. The supported values are: CSS color string, including hex and rgb or function(point) - user-defined function that will be evaluated for each point. Returning undefined will assume the default series color..
            </summary>

BoundAttributes.Name: ColorField
BoundAttributes.Documentation:
<summary>
            The data field containing the point color.** Applicable for column, candlestick and ohlc series. **
            </summary>

BoundAttributes.Name: DownColor
BoundAttributes.Documentation:
<summary>

            </summary>

BoundAttributes.Name: DownColorField

            </summary>

BoundAttributes.Name: Gap

            </summary>

BoundAttributes.Name: LowField
BoundAttributes.Documentation:
<summary>
            The data field containing the low value.** Available for candlestick and ohlc series **
            </summary>

BoundAttributes.Name: MissingValues
BoundAttributes.Documentation:
<summary>

BoundAttributes.Name: Aggregate
BoundAttributes.Documentation:
<summary>
            The aggregate function to apply for date series.This function is used when a category (an year, month, etc.) contains two or more points. The function return value is displayed instead of the individual points.The supported values are: "avg" - the average of all values for the date period.; "count" - the number of values for the date period.; "max" - the highest value for the date period.; "min" - the lowest value for the date period.; "sum" - the sum of all values for the date period. Defaults to 0 if no data points are defined.; "sumOrNull" - the sum of all values for the date period. Defaults to null if no data points are defined.; "first" - the first value; function(values, series, dataItems, category) - user-defined aggregate function. Returns single value or data item. or object  - (compound aggregate) Applicable to "candlestick" and ohlc "series". Specifies the aggregate for each data item field..
            </summary>

            <remarks>
            Not used if the provided (see <see cref="P:Microsoft.AspNetCore.Mvc.TagHelpers.InputTagHelper.InputTypeName" />) or calculated "type" attribute value is

            <see cref="M:Microsoft.AspNetCore.Mvc.ViewFeatures.IHtmlGenerator.GenerateTextBox(Microsoft.AspNetCore.Mvc.Rendering.ViewContext,Microsoft.AspNetCore.Mvc.ViewFeatures.ModelExplorer,System.String,System.Object,System.String,System.Object)" />.
            </remarks>

            helper to call and the default <see cref="P:Microsoft.AspNetCore.Mvc.TagHelpers.InputTagHelper.Format" /> value. A default <see cref="P:Microsoft.AspNetCore.Mvc.TagHelpers.InputTagHelper.Format" /> is not calculated
            if the provided (see <see cref="P:Microsoft.AspNetCore.Mvc.TagHelpers.InputTagHelper.InputTypeName" />) or calculated "type" attribute value is <c>checkbox</c>,
            <c>hidden</c>, <c>password</c>, or <c>radio</c>.

TagHelpers.Name: Bind
TagHelpers.Documentation: Binds the provided expression to an attribute and a change event, based on the naming of the bind attribute. For example: @bind-value="..." and @bind-value:event="onchange" will assign the current value of the expression to the 'value' attribute, and assign a delegate that attempts to set the value to the 'onchange' attribute.

BoundAttributes.Name: @bind-...
BoundAttributes.Documentation: Binds the provided expression to an attribute and a change event, based on the naming of the bind attribute. For example: @bind-value="..." and @bind-value:event="onchange" will assign the current value of the expression to the 'value' attribute, and assign a delegate that attempts to set the value to the 'onchange' attribute.

BoundAttributeParameters.Name: format
BoundAttributeParameters.Documentation: Specifies a format to convert the value specified by the corresponding bind attribute. For example: @bind-value:format="..." will apply a format string to the value specified in @bind-value="...". The format string can currently only be used with expressions of type DateTime.

BoundAttributeParameters.Name: event
BoundAttributeParameters.Documentation: Specifies the event handler name to attach for change notifications for the value provided by the '@bind-...' attribute.

BoundAttributeParameters.Name: culture
BoundAttributeParameters.Documentation: Specifies the culture to use for conversions.

BoundAttributeParameters.Name: get
BoundAttributeParameters.Documentation: Specifies the expression to use for binding the value to the attribute.

BoundAttributeParameters.Name: set
BoundAttributeParameters.Documentation: Specifies the expression to use for updating the bound value when a new value is available.

BoundAttributeParameters.Name: after
BoundAttributeParameters.Documentation: Specifies an action to run after the new value has been set.
